   Saatchi Considers Shift
                                                                                                       

   Saatchi &amp; Saatchi is considering a management shakeup that
would streamline the holding company's staff and move three
executive directors to operating posts, industry executives
said.
   Within the next few months, Saatchi is likely to shift
Jeremy Sinclair, Terry Bannister and Roy Warman into
operating roles within the company's communications business,
an individual familiar with the company said. Mr. Sinclair
currently is Saatchi's deputy chairman, while Messrs.
Bannister and Warman are co-chief executives of Saatchi's ad
business.
   The anticipated changes stem from Saatchi's effort to sell
its troubled consulting businesses, and from the company's
appointment last year of Robert LouisDreyfus as chief
executive and Charles Scott as finance director. As a result,
the need for other senior executives to work on corporate
matters has diminished. Saatchi officials declined to
comment.
